## 7. Performance Considerations

- **Database Indexes**: Optimized for common queries (user_id, email, name)
- **Caching**: Redis for sessions and frequently accessed contact data
- **Connection Pooling**: PostgreSQL connection pooling to handle 1,000 users efficiently
- **Pagination**: 20 items per page to reduce payload size
- **Compression**: Gzip compression for API responses
- **CDN**: CloudFront for static assets

## 8. Security Features

- **JWT Authentication**: Token-based authentication with expiration
- **HTTPS/TLS**: All traffic encrypted in transit
- **Database Encryption**: RDS encryption at rest
- **Secrets Management**: AWS Secrets Manager for sensitive data
- **Rate Limiting**: 100 requests per 15 minutes per IP
- **Input Validation**: Schema validation on all inputs
- **SQL Injection Prevention**: Parameterized queries
- **CORS**: Restricted to frontend domain only

This architecture can handle 1,000 concurrent users with high availability, scalability, and security.

# CSS Code to Make All Text Boxes Visible

Here are several approaches depending on your needs:

## 1. **Basic Approach - Make Input Fields Visible**
```css
input[type="text"],
input[type="email"],
input[type="password"],
input[type="search"],
input[type="url"],
input[type="number"],
textarea,
select {
    visibility: visible !important;
    display: block !important;
    opacity: 1 !important;
}
```

## 2. **Comprehensive Approach - All Form Elements**
```css
/* Text inputs */
input[type="text"],
input[type="email"],
input[type="password"],
input[type="search"],
input[type="url"],
input[type="number"],
input[type="tel"],
textarea,
select,
.textbox,
.text-input {
    visibility: visible !important;
    display: block !important;
    opacity: 1 !important;
    pointer-events: auto !important;
    color: inherit !important;
}
```

## 3. **Universal Approach - All Elements**
```css
* {
    visibility: visible !important;
    opacity: 1 !important;
    display: block !important;
}
```

## 4. **Remove Hidden/Display:None Classes**
```css
.hidden,
.hide,
[hidden],
[style*="display: none"],
[style*="visibility: hidden"],
[style*="opacity: 0"] {
    display: block !important;
    visibility: visible !important;
    opacity: 1 !important;
}
```

## **Recommendation**
Use **Option 1 or 2** as they target specific elements without breaking page layout. Option 3 may cause layout issues since it affects all elements.

