```css
* {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-style: italic;
  opacity: 0.3;
}
```

**Explanation:**

- `*` - Universal selector that targets all elements
- `font-size: 20px;` - Increases font size to 20px
- `font-style: italic;` - Italicizes all text
- `opacity: 0.3;` - Applies 70% transparency (0.3 = 30% opaque, 70% transparent)

**Note:** Using the universal selector on all elements can impact performance on large pages. If you want to target specific elements only, replace `*` with your desired selectors (e.g., `body`, `.class-name`, etc.).

