# Remove Duplicates from Array in JavaScript

Here are several methods to remove duplicates:

## **Method 1: Using Set (Most Efficient)**
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = [...new Set(arr)];
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## **Method 2: Using Array.filter() with indexOf()**
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = arr.filter((item, index) => arr.indexOf(item) === index);
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## **Method 3: Using Array.reduce()**
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = arr.reduce((unique, item) => {
  return unique.includes(item) ? unique : [...unique, item];
}, []);
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## **Method 4: Using a Loop with Object**
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = [];
const seen = {};

arr.forEach(item => {
  if (!seen[item]) {
    uniqueArr.push(item);
    seen[item] = true;
  }
});
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## **Method 5: For Array of Objects**
```javascript
const arr = [
  { id: 1, name: 'John' },
  { id: 2, name: 'Jane' },
  { id: 1, name: 'John' }
];

const uniqueArr = Array.from(
  new Map(arr.map(item => [item.id, item])).values()
);
console.log(uniqueArr);
// [{ id: 1, name: 'John' }, { id: 2, name: 'Jane' }]
```

---

## **Performance Comparison**

| Method | Time | Space | Best For |
|--------|------|-------|----------|
| **Set** | O(n) | O(n) | ✅ **Most efficient** |
| filter + indexOf | O(n²) | O(n) | Small arrays |
| reduce | O(n²) | O(n) | Readability |
| Loop + Object | O(n) | O(n) | Large arrays |

## **Recommendation**
Use **Method 1 (Set)** for best performance and clean code:
```javascript
const uniqueArr = [...new Set([1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3])];
```

